The effects of stimulation as we currently understand them are quite
complex since the electrode size, electrode position with respect to the
orientation of neurons, stimulation frequency, pulse width, current
amplitude, and polarity can all have varying effects on underlying neu-
ral activity and consequent behavior

monkeys demonstrates the complexity of stimulation's effects on neural
activity whereby changes in the frequency and site of stimulation
resulted in opposite outcomes
