Paper: Thinking Ahead on Deep Brain Stimulation: An Analysis of the Ethical Implications of a Developing Technology:
- DBS lösen stimulationinduced mania aus => keine perfekte Technik/Technik macht Fehler
- specific bioethical issues such as medical risks, consent, patient selection, and justifiable new indications (Bell, Mathieu, and Racine 2009; Dunn et al. 2011)
- general features such as ethical challenges raised by DBS during research and clinical practice, respectively (Clausen2010)
- “the ethical future of DBS”(Bell et al. 2009) and “ethical challenges ahead” (Clausen2010)
- Our aim is not to give a general introduction of or overview to the ethical concerns regarding DBS already identified and discussed, since this has been done elsewhere (Clausen 2010; Schermer 2011)
- we choose to focus on the case of authenticity—a recurring and ethically challenging concern raised by brain modulation (Kraemer 2013)

