Paper: Ethical brain stimulation – neuroethics of deep brain stimulation in research and clinical practice
Analysing neuroethical and clinical literature, five major topics concerning the ethics of DBS in clinical practice were identified:
- thorough examination and weighing of risks and benefits;
- selecting patients fairly;
- protecting the health of children in paediatric DBS;
- special issues concerning patients’ autonomy;
- the normative impact of quality of life measurements.
